      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a weird loud humming sound but the fan isnt actually spinning. its just sitting there vibrating and humming. what could be causing that and is it safe for me to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming ac unit without spinning fan can be a bit unsettling, but don't worry, it's likely not a sign of an imminent disaster. The humming sound is probably caused by the compressor or fan motor, which is still running, but not spinning. It's a bit like a stealthy little creature, hiding in plain sight, but still making noise. You might be able to identify the source by checking the unit's electrical connections and ensuring they're secure. \n\nHowever, I would advise against going near the unit until you're sure it's safe. You don't want to risk getting zapped by a live electrical wire, especially if you're not familiar with the unit's inner workings. It's better to leave it to a professional, or at the very least, someone with more experience in dealing with these sorts of issues. \n\nIf you're still concerned, you can try checking the unit's circuit breaker or fuse box to see if the breaker has tripped or a fuse has blown. If that's not the case, it's probably best to call a professional HVAC technician to take a look. They'll be able to diagnose the issue and fix it without putting you or yourself at risk.",
